Product Requirement Document (PRD) Addendum: AI Operations Co-Pilot & Feel-Good Study Coach
Status: Ready for Implementation
Author: Product Lead
Target Stack: Next.js 16 (App Router), Supabase (Postgres + Auth), Groq API via Vercel AI SDK, Inngest, Zustand, Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui.
1. Feature Overview & Objectives
This document serves as an isolated feature specification for adding an Agentic AI Study Coach to the existing SpaceLinear ecosystem.
Instead of acting as a static text assistant, this feature bridges conversational interaction with real-time app execution. It combines Feel-Good Productivity coaching pillars with autonomous database actions to automate manual workflow scaffolding (creating subjects, topics, and inserting initial MDX structures).
2. Core Functional Pillars (The Unified Persona)
The AI Coach must seamlessly merge two operational identities within a single conversation loop:
2.1 The Feel-Good Productivity Blueprint
Whenever a user interacts with the coach panel, the assistant must structure its conversational replies around five core behavioral rules:
Initial Discovery Framework: The coach must actively prompt the user to declare how many subjects they are currently balancing and what core topics need structural breakdown instead of waiting passively for manual setup.
Prioritization Mapping: The coach must guide the user to identify exactly one "Daily Adventure" (the highest leverage topic/task that defines a successful day) and two "Side Quests" (health, lifestyle, or break-focused activities).
The Priority Rule: If the user states they "do not have time" for a critical learning block or side quest, the coach must gently remind them that time constraints are fundamentally a reflection of priority.
The 3 Ps Strategy: Before committing massive learning structures to the database, the coach must challenge the user to define their entry across the 3 Ps:
Play: How can they make interacting with this specific flashcard or topic inherently engaging?
Power: How can they maximize personal control over how they digest this topic?
People: Who is their designated study peer, classmate, or accountability anchor for this concept?
The Unblock Method (Follow-Through): If a user expresses procrastination or overwhelm regarding a topic, the coach must systematically walk them through diagnosing Clarity, Courage, and Inertia, breaking the target topic down into frictionless chunks.
2.2 Agentic Abilities (Database Tooling)
The coach must be given permission to autonomously execute database mutations when the user approves a learning path in chat.
       +--------------------------------------------+
       |   Conversational Intent (Chat Prompt)       |
       +--------------------------------------------+
                             |
                             v
       +--------------------------------------------+
       |   Groq LLM Engine (Multi-Step Evaluation)  |
       +--------------------------------------------+
                 |                        |
        (Calls Tool 1)           (Calls Tool 2)
                 v                        v
+------------------------+      +-------------------------------+
|  `createSubject()`     |      |  `createTopic()`              |
|  Inserts record into   |      |  Inserts record into `topics` |
|  `subjects` table      |      |  mapped to the `subjectId`    |
+------------------------+      +-------------------------------+
3. Technical Specifications & Tool Design
The endpoint (/api/coach/agent/route.ts) utilizes the Vercel AI SDK to expose tools directly to the Groq model (llama-3.3-70b-versatile).
3.1 Exposed LLM Tools
The agent has access to two explicit local execution handlers. Every tool operation must strictly extract the server-validated user context (auth.users(id)) to enforce Row Level Security (RLS).
1. createSubject
Purpose: Sets up a high-level bucket for grouping notes and flashcards.
Parameters:
name (string, required): The title of the domain (e.g., "Algorithm Design").
description (string, optional): Contextual scope.
Action: Direct database insertion into the subjects table. Returns the newly generated subjectId.
2. createTopic
Purpose: Scaffolds an active recall item due immediately for review.
Parameters:
subjectId (uuid, required): The parent reference id.
title (string, required): The specific flashcard/note item (e.g., "Dynamic Programming").
description (string, required): High-level breakdown summary.
content (string, optional): Baseline markdown structure.
Action: Direct insertion into the topics table. It must initialize the tracking state to 'new', tag it with ['ai-scaffolded'], and stamp next_review_date to the current system date so it automatically appears in the user's Today review queue.
4. UI/UX Additions & Interaction Logic
Component Placement: A modern, collapsable slide-out utility panel or split-screen interface integrated alongside the primary application layout grids.
Diagnostic Execution Streams: When tools run in the background (createSubject or createTopic), the chat container must intercept the tool lifecycle updates and display them as inline operational tags (e.g., ⚙️ Building Subject: Web Engineering...) so the user can witness the agentic adjustments transparently.
Cache Revalidation Workflow: To eliminate stale screen instances, the client-side interaction block must hook into the chat interface's lifecycle (onFinish). When a sequence completes, it must programmatically trigger a cash invalidation cycle for TanStack Query keys ['subjects'] and ['topics'], providing instant, non-blocking screen updates across SpaceLinear.